          <term>harmonic</term> if <m>\Delta u = u_{xx} + u_{yy} = 0</m>.
          Let <m>a = (a_1,a_2)</m> and define <m>v(x) = u(x + a)</m>.
          Show that if <m>u</m> is harmonic on <m>\Omega</m>,
          then <m>v</m> is harmonic on <m>\Omega - a</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <hint>
        <p>
          Compute <m>v_x, v_{xx}, v_y, v_{yy}</m> using the chain rule.
        </p>
      </hint>
